    {
      "id": "bfcffe3c-98f3-4b5a-a231-c9837abe0bf2",
      "name": "Gemini Research Agent",
      "implementationType": "javascript",
      "outputType": "respond_to_ai",
      "openaiSpec": {
        "name": "gemini_autonomous_research_agent",
        "description": "Execute a fully autonomous multi-step deep research loop. Employs a sandboxed browser context to dynamically download, scrape, and extract text from web HTML, PDFs, and Excel Spreadsheets, using a recursive Gemini 3.5 Flash-Lite logic engine to generate secondary search queries, follow specific document download links, compile data tables, and output a highly integrated fact synthesis report.",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "max_steps": {
              "type": "number",
              "description": "The maximum number of autonomous loop iterations to perform (1-5, defaults to 3)."
            },
            "initial_urls": {
              "type": "array",
              "description": "Optional list of initial URLs to scrape first (e.g. direct download links or specific PDF documents).",
              "items": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            },
            "target_query": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The precise information objective or quantitative/historical target. (e.g., 'US military spending total by year from 2015 to 2025')"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "target_query"
          ]
        }
      },
      "code": "async function gemini_autonomous_research_agent(params, userSettings) {\n  const { target_query, initial_urls, max_steps = 3 } = params;\n  const proxyBase = (userSettings.workerUrl || 'https://unified-proxy.creativeappmaking.workers.dev').replace(/\\/$/, '');\n  const exaApiKey = userSettings.exa_api_key;\n  const geminiApiKey = userSettings.google_api_key;\n  \n  if (!exaApiKey || !geminiApiKey) {\n    return {\n      status: 'error',\n      message: 'Required API Keys are missing. Please enter your Exa and Google Gemini API keys in the plugin settings.'\n    };\n  }\n\n  const geminiUrl = `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/interactions?key=${geminiApiKey}`;\n  const today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\n  \n  const logs = [];\n  const scrapedUrls = new Set();\n  const searchQueriesExecuted = [];\n  const corpus = [];\n  \n  function log(msg) {\n    console.log(`[Research Agent] ${msg}`);\n    logs.push(`[${new Date().toISOString().split('T')[1].slice(0, 8)}] ${msg}`);\n  }\n\n  function sleep(ms) {\n    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n  }\n\n  // HTML cleanup function\n  function htmlToMarkdown(htmlString) {\n    try {\n      const parser = new DOMParser();\n      const doc = parser.parseFromString(htmlString, 'text/html');\n      \n      const toRemove = doc.querySelectorAll('script, style, iframe, nav, footer, header, noscript, svg, img, form');\n      toRemove.forEach(el => el.remove());\n\n      const mainContent = doc.querySelector('article, main, #content, .content, #main-content') || doc.body;\n      if (!mainContent) return '';\n\n      let text = mainContent.innerText || mainContent.textContent || '';\n      text = text.replace(/[ \\t]+/g, ' ')\n                 .replace(/\\n\\s*\\n/g, '\\n\\n')\n                 .trim();\n      return text.slice(0, 15000);\n    } catch (e) {\n      return htmlString.slice(0, 10000);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Dynamic PDF.js Loader\n  async function loadPdfJS() {\n    if (window.pdfjsLib) return window.pdfjsLib;\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n      const script = document.createElement('script');\n      script.src = 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf.js/2.16.105/pdf.min.js';\n      script.onload = () => {\n        window.pdfjsLib.GlobalWorkerOptions.workerSrc = 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/pdf.js/2.16.105/pdf.worker.min.js';\n        resolve(window.pdfjsLib);\n      };\n      script.onerror = () => reject(new Error('Failed to load PDF.js'));\n      document.head.appendChild(script);\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Dynamic SheetJS Loader\n  async function loadSheetJS() {\n    if (window.XLSX) return window.XLSX;\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n      const script = document.createElement('script');\n      script.src = 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/xlsx/0.18.5/xlsx.full.min.js';\n      script.onload = () => resolve(window.XLSX);\n      script.onerror = () => reject(new Error('Failed to load SheetJS'));\n      document.head.appendChild(script);\n    });\n  }\n\n  async function extractTextFromPdfData(arrayBuffer) {\n    try {\n      const pdfjs = await loadPdfJS();\n      const loadingTask = pdfjs.getDocument({ data: arrayBuffer });\n      const pdf = await loadingTask.promise;\n      let fullText = '';\n      const maxPages = Math.min(pdf.numPages, 10);\n      for (let pageNum = 1; pageNum <= maxPages; pageNum++) {\n        const page = await pdf.getPage(pageNum);\n        const textContent = await page.getTextContent();\n        const pageText = textContent.items.map(item => item.str).join(' ');\n        fullText += `[Page ${pageNum}]\\n${pageText}\\n\\n`;\n      }\n      return fullText;\n    } catch (err) {\n      return `[PDF text extraction failed: ${err.message}]`;\n    }\n  }\n\n  async function extractTextFromExcelData(arrayBuffer) {\n    try {\n      const xlsx = await loadSheetJS();\n      const workbook = xlsx.read(arrayBuffer, { type: 'array' });\n      let fullText = '';\n      const sheetNames = workbook.SheetNames.slice(0, 3);\n      for (const sheetName of sheetNames) {\n        const sheet = workbook.Sheets[sheetName];\n        const csv = xlsx.utils.sheet_to_csv(sheet);\n        fullText += `[Sheet: ${sheetName}]\\n${csv.slice(0, 10000)}\\n\\n`;\n      }\n      return fullText;\n    } catch (err) {\n      return `[Excel text extraction failed: ${err.message}]`;\n    }\n  }\n\n  async function scrapeUrl(url) {\n    const fetchUrl = `${proxyBase}/proxy/${url}`;\n    const controller = new AbortController();\n    const id = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 15000);\n    \n    try {\n      const res = await fetch(fetchUrl, { signal: controller.signal });\n      clearTimeout(id);\n      if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP Error ${res.status}`);\n      \n      const contentType = res.headers.get('content-type') || '';\n      if (contentType.includes('application/pdf') || url.toLowerCase().endsWith('.pdf')) {\n        const arrayBuffer = await res.arrayBuffer();\n        const text = await extractTextFromPdfData(arrayBuffer);\n        return { type: 'pdf', text };\n      } else if (contentType.includes('spreadsheet') || contentType.includes('excel') || url.toLowerCase().endsWith('.xlsx') || url.toLowerCase().endsWith('.xls')) {\n        const arrayBuffer = await res.arrayBuffer();\n        const text = await extractTextFromExcelData(arrayBuffer);\n        return { type: 'excel', text };\n      } else {\n        const html = await res.text();\n        return { type: 'html', text: htmlToMarkdown(html) };\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      clearTimeout(id);\n      throw err;\n    }\n  }\n\n  async function runExaSearch(searchQuery) {\n    const body = {\n      query: searchQuery,\n      numResults: 5,\n      type: 'auto',\n      contents: {\n        text: { maxCharacters: 15000 }\n      }\n    };\n\n    const res = await fetch(`${proxyBase}/exa/search`, {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n        'x-api-key': exaApiKey\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify(body)\n    });\n\n    if (!res.ok) {\n      throw new Error(`Exa API Error: ${res.status} ${res.statusText}`);\n    }\n\n    const data = await res.json();\n    return data.results || [];\n  }\n\n  async function callGemini(systemInstruction, userPrompt, responseSchema) {\n    const payload = {\n      model: 'gemini-3.5-flash-lite',\n      input: userPrompt,\n      system_instruction: systemInstruction,\n      generation_config: {\n        max_output_tokens: 8192\n      }\n    };\n\n    if (responseSchema) {\n      payload.response_format = [\n        {\n          type: 'text',\n          mime_type: 'application/json',\n          schema: responseSchema\n        }\n      ];\n    }\n\n    const res = await fetch(geminiUrl, {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify(payload)\n    });\n\n    if (!res.ok) {\n      const errText = await res.text().catch(() => '');\n      throw new Error(`Gemini API Error: ${res.status} ${res.statusText}${errText ? ' - ' + errText : ''}`);\n    }\n\n    const data = await res.json();\n    \n    if (data.output_text) return data.output_text;\n\n    if (data.steps && Array.isArray(data.steps)) {\n      for (const step of data.steps) {\n        if (step.type === 'model_output' && Array.isArray(step.content)) {\n          for (const part of step.content) {\n            if (part.type === 'text' && part.text) {\n              return part.text;\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    return JSON.stringify(data);\n  }\n\n  function extractJSON(text) {\n    if (!text) return null;\n    let clean = text.trim();\n    clean = clean.replace(/^```json\\s*/i, '').replace(/^```\\s*/i, '').replace(/```\\s*$/i, '');\n    const startIdx = clean.indexOf('{');\n    const endIdx = clean.lastIndexOf('}');\n    if (startIdx !== -1 && endIdx !== -1) {\n      clean = clean.substring(startIdx, endIdx + 1);\n    }\n    return JSON.parse(clean);\n  }\n\n  // Initialize loop states\n  let currentStep = 1;\n  let nextQueries = [target_query];\n  let nextUrlsToScrape = initial_urls ? [...initial_urls] : [];\n  let finalReport = null;\n\n  log(`Starting Autonomous Research Agent for query: \"${target_query}\"`);\n\n  const geminiResponseSchema = {\n    type: 'object',\n    properties: {\n      status: { type: 'string', enum: ['completed', 'continue'] },\n      explanation: { type: 'string' },\n      next_exa_queries: { type: 'array', items: { type: 'string' } },\n      next_urls_to_scrape: { type: 'array', items: { type: 'string' } },\n      synthesized_report: { type: 'string' }\n    },\n    required: ['status', 'explanation', 'next_exa_queries', 'next_urls_to_scrape', 'synthesized_report']\n  };\n\n  while (currentStep <= max_steps) {\n    log(`--- STEP ${currentStep} of ${max_steps} ---`);\n\n    // 1. Execute Exa Searches\n    const searchPromises = nextQueries.map(async (q) => {\n      if (searchQueriesExecuted.includes(q)) return [];\n      searchQueriesExecuted.push(q);\n      log(`Executing Exa search: \"${q}\"`);\n      try {\n        const results = await runExaSearch(q);\n        log(`Exa search returned ${results.length} results.`);\n        return results;\n      } catch (e) {\n        log(`Exa search failed for \"${q}\": ${e.message}`);\n        return [];\n      }\n    });\n\n    const searchResults = await Promise.all(searchPromises);\n    \n    // Process search results and add URLs to the queue\n    searchResults.flat().forEach(r => {\n      if (r.url && !scrapedUrls.has(r.url)) {\n        nextUrlsToScrape.push(r.url);\n        // Also cache Exa text to corpus\n        if (r.text) {\n          corpus.push({\n            url: r.url,\n            title: r.title || 'Exa Snippet',\n            type: r.url.toLowerCase().endsWith('.pdf') ? 'pdf_snippet' : 'html_snippet',\n            text: r.text.slice(0, 10000),\n            source: 'exa_search'\n          });\n        }\n      }\n    });\n\n    // 2. Scrape target URLs (Limit to top 3 unvisited URLs per step to prevent token explosion)\n    const urlsToProcess = [...new Set(nextUrlsToScrape)].filter(u => !scrapedUrls.has(u)).slice(0, 3);\n    nextUrlsToScrape = nextUrlsToScrape.filter(u => !urlsToProcess.includes(u));\n\n    if (urlsToProcess.length > 0) {\n      log(`Scraping/parsing target URLs: ${JSON.stringify(urlsToProcess)}`);\n      const scrapePromises = urlsToProcess.map(async (url) => {\n        scrapedUrls.add(url);\n        try {\n          const scraped = await scrapeUrl(url);\n          log(`Successfully scraped (${scraped.type}): ${url} (${scraped.text.length} chars)`);\n          return {\n            url,\n            title: url,\n            type: scraped.type,\n            text: scraped.text,\n            source: 'scraper'\n          };\n        } catch (e) {\n          log(`Failed to scrape ${url}: ${e.message}`);\n          return {\n            url,\n            title: url,\n            type: 'failed',\n            text: `[Scrape failed: ${e.message}]`,\n            source: 'scraper'\n          };\n        }\n      });\n\n      const scrapeResults = await Promise.all(scrapePromises);\n      scrapeResults.forEach(r => {\n        const idx = corpus.findIndex(c => c.url === r.url);\n        if (idx !== -1) {\n          corpus[idx] = r;\n        } else {\n          corpus.push(r);\n        }\n      });\n    } else {\n      log(\"No new target URLs to scrape this step.\");\n    }\n\n    // 3. Reason with Gemini 3.5 Flash-Lite\n    log(\"Invoking Gemini 3.5 Flash-Lite for synthesis & direction...\");\n    const systemInstruction = `Today's date is ${today}.\\nYour objective is to find high-precision, quantitative, and deeply researched answers for: \"${target_query}\".\\nYou are on step ${currentStep} of ${max_steps}.\\n\\nEvaluate the provided research corpus. Your job is to extract exact statistics, chronological data, and specific financial/macroeconomic tables if present.\\n\\nIf the corpus contains the complete and final answers with enough details to comprehensively satisfy the query, or if this is the final step (${max_steps}), set \"status\" to \"completed\" and synthesize your final, structured \"synthesized_report\".\\nThe \"synthesized_report\" must be an exhaustive, highly structured academic-quality Markdown report with tables, year-by-year spending breakdowns, citations of the URLs used, and an evaluation of any contradictions or revisions.\\n\\nIf you are missing key details (e.g., you found a PDF link or an Excel sheet link but need to scrape it, or you need to do another targeted search to cross-verify), set \"status\" to \"continue\". Explain what is missing in \"explanation\" and suggest:\\n1. Up to 2 highly-targeted search queries to execute on Exa (under \"next_exa_queries\").\\n2. Up to 3 specific URLs to fetch/scrape next (under \"next_urls_to_scrape\").\\n\\nCRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS:\\n- If you notice links to PDFs (.pdf) or spreadsheets (.xlsx, .xls) in the text that are highly relevant to the query, extract those URLs and put them into \"next_urls_to_scrape\" so the agent can scrape them in the next step.\\n- NEVER tell the user to check links themselves. Synthesize everything.\\n- Output strictly a JSON object matching the requested schema.`;\n\n    const corpusSummary = corpus.map((c, idx) => `\\nSource ${idx + 1}:\\nURL: ${c.url}\\nTitle: ${c.title}\\nType: ${c.type}\\nSource: ${c.source}\\nContent Snippet:\\n${c.text.slice(0, 15000)}\\n------------------------\\n`).join('\\n\\n');\n\n    const userPrompt = `Target Query: \"${target_query}\"\\nCurrent Research Step: ${currentStep} of ${max_steps}\\nSearch Queries Executed So Far: ${JSON.stringify(searchQueriesExecuted)}\\nURLs Scraped So Far: ${JSON.stringify(Array.from(scrapedUrls))}\\n\\nResearch Corpus:\\n${corpusSummary}`;\n\n    try {\n      const geminiOutputText = await callGemini(systemInstruction, userPrompt, geminiResponseSchema);\n      const geminiResponse = extractJSON(geminiOutputText);\n      \n      if (!geminiResponse) {\n        throw new Error(\"Failed to parse Gemini JSON output.\");\n      }\n\n      log(`Gemini response: Status = ${geminiResponse.status}. Explanation: ${geminiResponse.explanation}`);\n\n      if (geminiResponse.status === 'completed' || currentStep === max_steps) {\n        finalReport = geminiResponse.synthesized_report || \"No report was generated.\";\n        break;\n      } else {\n        nextQueries = geminiResponse.next_exa_queries || [];\n        (geminiResponse.next_urls_to_scrape || []).forEach(u => {\n          if (!scrapedUrls.has(u)) nextUrlsToScrape.push(u);\n        });\n        \n        if (nextQueries.length === 0 && nextUrlsToScrape.length === 0) {\n          log(\"No new actions generated by Gemini. Finalizing research.\");\n          finalReport = geminiResponse.synthesized_report || \"Research concluded early due to lack of next actions.\";\n          break;\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (e) {\n      log(`Gemini invocation failed: ${e.message}`);\n      if (currentStep === max_steps) {\n        finalReport = `Failed during research reasoning on the final step: ${e.message}. Compiled corpus is available.`;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n\n    currentStep++;\n    await sleep(1000);\n  }\n\n  log(\"Research Agent completed its run.\");\n  \n  return {\n    status: \"success\",\n    target_query: target_query,\n    steps_run: currentStep > max_steps ? max_steps : currentStep,\n    scraped_urls: Array.from(scrapedUrls),\n    search_queries_executed: searchQueriesExecuted,\n    synthesized_report: finalReport,\n    sources_count: corpus.length,\n    sources_summary: corpus.map(c => ({ url: c.url, title: c.title, type: c.type, status: c.text.includes('failed') ? 'failed' : 'scraped' })),\n    run_logs: logs\n  };\n}"
    }
  ],
  "overviewMarkdown": "## **Gemini Autonomous Research Agent 🔬**\n\nThis plugin functions as an autonomous, multi-step search, scrape, and reason engine. It runs recursively inside a single JavaScript tool call, executing multiple rounds of neural web search, downloading documents, and synthesizing findings before handing the complete grounded results back to the parent LLM.\n\n### **Features**\n\n- **Autonomous Iteration Loop**: Runs up to 5 steps of search-and-scrape reasoning. Gemini 3.5 Flash-Lite is recursively fed intermediate results and decides whether to continue, which PDF or Excel links to explore next, or when to synthesize the final report.\n- **Full PDF Parser (CORS-Safe)**: Dynamically loads the `pdf.js` parsing library completely client-side in the browser. Reads, extracts, and summarizes text from complex PDF manuals, legislative bills, or reports.\n- **Full Excel Spreadsheet Parser (CORS-Safe)**: Dynamically loads the SheetJS (`xlsx`) spreadsheet parser. Downloads Excel sheets and converts tabular sheets into plain CSV matrices that can be read directly by the agent.\n- **Unified Cloudflare Proxy Compliance**: Routes all scrapes through your self-hosted proxy to completely eliminate CORS and Direct IP Access blocks.\n\n### **Setup Instructions**\n\n1. Ensure you have your self-hosted **Cloudflare Multi-API Proxy Worker** set up.\n2. Provide your **Exa API Key** and your **Google Gemini API Key** (from Google AI Studio).\n3. Save the Custom Tool in TypingMind and use it whenever you require high-precision multi-year, socioeconomic, or tabular historical data.",
  "authenticationType": "AUTH_TYPE_NONE"
}
